description.narrative: Increased number people in rural, urban and peri-urban areas, small towns and at schools and health centres have access to adequate and equitable sanitation and hygiene services and are empowered to end open defecation., which contributes to Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Sanitation. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, increased numbers of people, especially girls and women, socially excluded groups and others in vulnerable situations, are healthy and live in resilient communities, access affordable and equitable WASH services and abandon open defecation

description.narrative: The sanitation and hygiene promotion using the Community Led Total Sanitation (CLTS) at community level and the provision of sanitation facilities, hygiene promotion at the institutional level reached 163,877 people including 37,339 people living in 76 ODF communities; 38,170 pupils (19,900 boys & 18,270 girls) in 86 schools and 88,368 patients from 89 health facilities. Progress is however constrained due to limited funding for sustainable programmes. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
